author: Muhammad Zulfadly Bin Abdul Manap
text: The gym floor is spacious after renovation. It is more powerlifting friendly - 3 deadlift platforms, 3 squat racks. Couldn't say the same for the plates which are aging and worn. Plenty of machines for legs like hip thrust, hack squats. Too bad most of the gym-goera here couldn't appreciate this. They have a spacious functional training area and group classes too. There are plenty of shower stalls here as well. This would be an ideal outlet for me if it wasn't for the distance (i live in Yishun).

author: Ribeye
text:
Anytime Fitness at West Coast Plaza is a modern, well-equipped gym. Accessible 24/7, this branch is particularly spacious.
With a wide range of cardio and strength training equipment, a functional training area, free weights, and spaces for class.
The gym's atmosphere is conducive and well maintained. Overall a clean, spacious environment for users in the area.

author: Jenny Yew
text:
I've been training at Anytime Fitness West Coast for over two months now, and I just want to give a big shoutout to my personal trainer, David. I have a torn meniscus and my knee tends to get inflamed very easily, so I was initially quite hesitant about strength training. But David has been incredibly attentive and knowledgeableâ€”always adjusting the workouts to suit my condition while still helping me make real progress.

Over the past couple of months, Iâ€™ve noticed a big improvementâ€”my knee gets less inflamed, and my leg feels noticeably stronger. Iâ€™m really happy with the results so far and grateful for the care and guidance Iâ€™ve received.

Also, I really like this outletâ€”itâ€™s spacious, clean and well-equipped, which makes the training experience even more comfortable and enjoyable. Highly recommend David and this location if youâ€™re looking for a supportive and effective training environment, especially if youâ€™re working with an injury or need a more tailored approach.

author: ACKSHAL R
text:
I've been training with Lisa for the past few months, and I'm impressed with her ability to quickly assess my strengths and weaknesses and develop a training plan that addresses my specific goals. She is also very patient, understanding, and friendly.

I saw many negative comments about the gym and gym atmosphere. Don't believe those reviews. The gym is very clean, and the staff and trainers are very friendly.

text: Before joining Anytime Fitness I had no knowledge about training in the gym. But after having training sessions with trainer Lisa, she has helped me give an introduction on how to use the gym equipment and enjoy working out. Highly recommend joining, gym is open 24 hours making it extremely convenient for busy students like me.

author: Engracia Toh
text:
Staff are friendly and the gym is big. It's not as fancy as those central gyms (like city hall) but there's a lot of equipment and space (and isn't as horribly crowded as central gyms lol). It also looks nicer after the recent renovation. Definitely good if you live in the area.

Also, my trainer Lisa is very friendly and helps a lot with my workout form and motivation at the gym. Have seen tangible improvements in the past 4 months (I go around 2-3 times a week: 1-2 pt sessions and 1 session on my own). Would definitely recommend for people with no experience trying to get over gym anxiety and build their basics

But female toilet soap dispenser still keeps getting stuck :<. Would appreciate if that was fixed. Also, if possible, a more advanced body composition machine would be great to help track our gains!

author: Shrigauri Kanna

author: Moony Lmm
text: Terrible sound system and song choice. I am not sure itâ€™s club or gym. Low maintenance!. If one machine is out of order, it will take forever to be repaired. Cable machine is terribly old. Who knows? they never care of paying customers anymore after they got enough base people to get running. Treadmill belts - they are rusty and making a lot of noises, at least two out of three I tried. Hopefully there is another competitive gym providers in the neighborhoods and I am happy to switch.

author: debbie wilson
text: Recently the music at night has been good! Please keep playing this music playlist :)

The whole gym ensues a very unwelcoming vibes, unfriendly admin and PT! Allow friends who are not a staff there to enter the â€œstaff onlyâ€ room and stayed in there for quite a while, the R&R there excludes their own friends and relative of course. The admin and PT there often show the unfriendly and unhappy faces as if members owe them a living! Equipments were not well maintained too, when things are down, they will take their own sweet time to have them repaired. Feedbacks often went unheard and ignored. Limited lockers too, such a big gym yet only a few lockers. Other AF we been to were very well maintained with friendly and helpful staffs but definitely not this one!

author: Yong L
text:
One of the AF gym outlets which is not so well managed.

Covid-19 poster remains on the wall at water cooler. Water source from water cooler tasted funky. No maintenance at all. If a poster remains on the wall, let us not talked about having filters changed at appropriate intervals. Water cooler located in toilet can be quite unhygienic too. Such a poster which is no longer valid remains on the wall for such a long time says a lot of managing the facility.

Gym lacks(not enough) proper clean, up paper towels and sanitiser.

Would the owner even care?

author: Elaine Ng
text: Honestly if you have tried our other AF gyms you will realise that the customer service is seriously lacking at this outlet. Joined this outlet more than a year ago, have no issues with the staff or whatsoever. Just that some PT can be very rude to us at times but not that we cannot tolerate. The other day there was a guy using the female toilet at the gym around 11pm, informed the gym about this incident as itâ€™s honestly very unsafe for female users of the gym if this continues. However, I did not even get a reply from the staff, just a blue tick. Even if you do not bother, at least if you have basic manners, perhaps just a PR reply will do. But I guess nobody cares about whether youâ€™re safe or not as long as youâ€™re paying for your membership fees. Seriously contemplating switching to Pasir Panjang gym, the customer service is wonderful and they make every gym user feel valued despite us not paying any fees to them.

author: Will
text:
Soap dispenser in female toilet is always malfunctioning. At least for a year.

No square towel tissue and full of hair on toilet counter that's with the sink and hairdryer.

Wifi speed from initial starting very good to lousy. Worse than 3g speed. Today 6mbps considered fast.

5g only for admin and I wonder what do they need such high speed when members are experiencing such low speed.

Told trainer before, no use. Still v slow. Network is so slow that page is always spinning.

Machines breaking down. Repair is slow. Place is also very stuffy. Like saving on aircon.

author: Julian Ang
text:
Large gym space but cramped free weights area. Has 50kg dumbbells which are awesome. Counted 3 racks which is also awesome. Change rooms have showers but they really could be a lot brighter. New Precor treadmills, ellipticals and bikes. Generally empty before 0930/1000 hrs so that's great and there's AC by about 0800hrs (I think).

Overall, it's a nice, large space with a mainly expatriate clientele that's not quite your gym nut, so expect a bit more machine/bench hogging. I'd go again but defo not during slightly busier periods.

author: J
text:
The Three Musketeers. Harry, Ron & Hermione. Nirvana. Great things come in trios. And that's what keeping this place from being great, as the third squat rack here doesn't have a bar for some reason. It would be great to have more bars overall, as the two mats for dead-lifting/rows are also empty.

Other than that, everything looks great.

EDIT: There are now three power racks each with bars plus a smith machine, thanks!
